title: Frank Lloyd Wright Coonley Playhouse House Window Earrings
description:
This earring features a detail from a playful art glass window design created by Frank Lloyd Wright in 1912. With asymmetrical geometric designs and suggestions of flags, balloons, and confetti, the brightly colored windows bring to mind a parade—a fun theme appropriate for a children's playroom.

Details:

• Solid brass

• Electro-plated with a hematite finish

• Hand enameled

• Posts are plated hematite

• Hangs approx. 2.25"
